Description:
Annotation on the envelope: "Rubensfeier Antwerpen 1940" addressed (inside) to "Herrn Prof. Dr. H. G. Evers Waldstrasse 43 6101 Traisa"

- Invitation to the ceremony in memory of Rubens in Antwerp dated 1940
- Rubenscantate libretto
- Invitation to an event for those who were involved in the Rubens commemoration (dated 12.11.1940)
- Reproductions of churches and paintings
- Article: 'Rubens in Siegen und Antwerpen. Dr. Kruse und Prof. van Roosbroek sprachen zu Beginn der Rubensfeier'
- Article: 'De eerste dag der Rubensherdenking te Antwerpen' in "Het algemeen Nieuws" dated 1940
- Article: 'De Rubensherdenking te Antwerpen' in "Het algemeen Nieuws" dated 19.11.1940
- Article: 'De Rubensherdenking te Antwerpen beleefde Zondag haar hoogtepunt' in "Volk en Staat" dated 19.11.1940
- Article: 'Pieter Pauwel Rubens te Antwerpen gehildigd' in "Volk en Staat" dated 17.11.1940
- Antwerp city maps
- Correspondence about Rubens commemoration dated 1939
- Adverts of Rubens commemoration (Antwerp, June-October 1940)
- Notes
